The paper introduces a new method for reinforcement learning using quantum hardware, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of quantum annealers, which falls under the category of quantum computing, making cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of Boltzmann machines, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques, which falls under the category of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
